South America
---
Brazil
- Affected children. Fri 8 Mar 2019. (reported) As the children of what's sometimes called the "Generation Zika" turn 3, they continue to suffer from a broad range of problems. Symptoms include muscle stiffness and weakness, seizures, vision impairment, and trouble swallowing. Most toddlers with CZS [congenital Zika syndrome] cannot walk or talk, and may never be able to. Doctors do know that specialized therapy can help, but the variety of symptoms require visits to multiple specialists many days a week. Unfortunately, health and money challenges are not the only issues to overcome. The outbreak left hundreds of mothers struggling emotionally as well. Many told CBS News they felt left behind or forgotten.
https://www.cbsnews.com/news/zika-virus-children-of-the-outbreak-cbsn-originals/

